• Lambic beer is aged for several years in oak barrels, which helps develop the complex flavors. Blends of young and aged Lambic beers are also common.

• Commonly used grains in Lambic beer include malted barley, unmalted wheat, and stale hops. The hops are used more for their preservative qualities than flavor.

• Some well-known Lambic beer brands are Cantillon, 3 Fonteinen, and Girardin.

Deleterious mutations often get eliminated from the gene pool over multiple generations.
